      <section eId="sec_CCP-2004">
        <num>CCP 2004</num>
        <heading>2004. Â Annulment for vices of substance; peremption of action</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2004__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A final judgment obtained by fraud or ill practices may be annulled.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2004__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An action to annul a judgment on these grounds must be brought within one year of the discovery by the plaintiff in the nullity action of the fraud or ill practices.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2004__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court may award reasonable attorney fees incurred by the prevailing party in an action to annul a judgment on these grounds.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111370</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
